
[1]palace-court

   PAL'ACE-COURT, n. The domestic court of the kings of Great Britain,
   which administers justice between the king's domestic servants. It is
   held once a week before the steward of the household and knight
   marshal; its jurisdiction extending twelve miles in circuit from his
   majesty's palace.
